    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "4ada41d1",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4ada41d1"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Choix de l'algorithme"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "0e8bb5bd",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0e8bb5bd"
      },
      "source": [
        "Il existe plusieurs algorithmes de regression. Pour ce TP nous nous contenterons de ceux implémenter dans le package `sklearn`.\n",
        "\n",
        "Le but ici étant de faire la prédiction du prix des maisons californiennes, nous voulons donc améliorer notre score de prédiction. Afin de bien comparer toutes les démarches mises en place il faut fixer un environnement. Ici nous allons choisir la métrique [RMSE](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.metrics.mean_squared_error.html#sklearn.metrics.mean_squared_error) pour ses bonnes propriétés.\n",
        "De plus, il est important d'avoir une baseline afin d'avoir déjà un score à améliorer.\n",
        "Dans notre cas nous allons utiliser la regression linéaire.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "817004a8",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "817004a8",
        "outputId": "19a29b21-1b09-4b7d-cca2-8473489647ac"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "X : (2043, 9)\n",
            "y : (2043,)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Variable cible\n",
        "y = df['target']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Features retenues\n",
        "features = [\n",
        "    'MedInc',\n",
        "    'AveRooms',\n",
        "    'AveOccup',\n",
        "    'Latitude',\n",
        "    'Longitude',\n",
        "    'PctTenents',\n",
        "    'ratio_chambres',\n",
        "    'densite_occupation',\n",
        "    'proche_cote'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "X = df[features]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"X : {X.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"y : {y.shape}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "68b38ad2",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "68b38ad2",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "ddd427f0-07a5-43d5-d60f-0c1af8753ccf"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "RMSE Régression Linéaire (baseline) : 0.7133\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X, y, test_size=0.5, random_state=0\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "LR = LinearRegression()\n",
        "y_pred = LR.fit(X_train, y_train).predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "rmse_baseline = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "print(f\"RMSE Régression Linéaire (baseline) : {rmse_baseline:.4f}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "8e092eb0",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8e092eb0"
      },
      "source": [
        "Il va être interessant ici de choisir le bon algorithme et les bonnes features.\n",
        "\n",
        "Ainsi les leviers d'action possible sont :\n",
        "\n",
        "- le choix de l'algorithme\n",
        "- les hyperparamètres de l'algorithme choisi\n",
        "- les features mises en entrée de l'algorithme (dans la variable X)\n",
        "\n",
        "Ainsi afin d'améliorer votre prédiction, il va être interessant de revenir souvent sur vos choix afin d'améliorer vos modèles."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "a60215c4",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "a60215c4"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Validation croisée\n",
        "\n",
        "La validation croisée permet d'éviter l'overfitting."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "c1d74e2b",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c1d74e2b",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "d2a93814-aef1-4922-fc0c-e4c2fb451339"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "RMSE moyen (validation croisée, 5 folds) : 0.7246\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
        "\n",
        "LR = LinearRegression()\n",
        "scores = -1 * cross_val_score(LR, X, y, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')\n",
        "rmse_cv = np.sqrt(np.mean(scores))\n",
        "print(f\"RMSE moyen (validation croisée, 5 folds) : {rmse_cv:.4f}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
